sec.p:
This study is an experimental randomized control trial that has been approved by the Ethics Committee of the Universiti Kebangsaan Malaysia Medical Centre (UKMMC) (Project Ethics Code: FF-280-2009). The participants were 35–60-year-old women recruited from the UKMMC records. These women must fulfil the following criteria:
body mass index (BMI) of less than 35 kg/m2;
SBP of 120–159 mmHg and DBP of 90–99 mmHg with or without treatment. If they are on antihypertensive or anticholesterol medications, they must be on only one medication of the same type and dose for at least six months;
normal liver, thyroid, and renal functions;
not taking any prescribed and/or traditional medications (apart from those stated in (b)) and supplements;
not smoking or drinking alcohol;
no other illnesses;
not pregnant;
have not experienced Swedish Massage Therapy.
